    <title>Save settings</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="Save settings">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to save settings, like the properties of a user of a group.</span>

   <span class='screenshot'>
     <img src="../../../../images/save_settings.png" alt='save settings screenshot'/>      
   </span>

  <p>
   In the properties list on the right of the <a href='./goto_user_management_tab.html'>user management tab</a>
   click on the save button (at the bottom of the list of properties).
  </p>

   <p>
    If you change your mind before you clicked the save button, click the cancel button. 
    <div class='alert-48 icon-text-48'>
     If you logout without clicking the cancel button, the new properties will also be saved. 
     This is generally a good thing, but know what you are doing when changing for example the
     admin password.
    </div>
   </p>

